      "excerpt": "A neighborhood-centered guide to events, civic life, and useful local information around White Plains.",
      "text": "A neighborhood-centered guide to events, civic life, and useful local information around White Plains.\n\nWhite Plains, New York\n\nWhat's happening in White Plains\n\nEvents, neighborhoods, and civic life in the county seat of Westchester.\n\nWPCNA helps keep neighborhood concerns, local events, and civic information easier to follow across White Plains.\n\nUpcoming68 events\n\nNeighborhoods43\n\nSourcesCity, Library, BID, WPPAC\n\nWhite Plains\n\nA closer look at the city\n\nViews pulled from the older WPCNA site, carried forward here so the homepage feels rooted in the place it serves.\n\nGolden hour\n\nAerial view\n\nComing Up\n\nUpcoming events\n\nA curated selection of public meetings, arts events, downtown happenings, and neighborhood programs.\n\nCatch Me If You Can\n\nApr 10, 2026 - May 3, 2026\n\nA spring run of the musical at the White Plains Performing Arts Center.\n\nWhite Plains in 1776 (History via Igloo)\n\nApr 22, 2026\n\nLearn about events in White Plains during the crucial year of 1776.\n\nLifting Up Westchester\n\nApr 22, 2026\n\nVictor Ortiz of Lifting Up Westchester will be available to provide information about essential social services available to patrons in the White Plains area.\n\nLearn about 3D Printing (in the Igloo)\n\nApr 22, 2026\n\nLearn about 3D printing and how to use the Library's 3D printing services.\n\nGetting Started with Genealogy\n\nApr 23, 2026\n\nJoin educator and genealogist Dennis Richmond, Jr.\n\nDowntown White Plains Wing Walk 2026\n\nApr 25, 2026\n\nA ticketed wing tasting across downtown White Plains, with voting and stops at local restaurants.\n\nNeighborhoods\n\nExplore White Plains\n\n43 neighborhoods from Downtown to Saxon Woods.\n\nCentral White Plains\n\nDowntown\n\nDowntown is the most walkable and built-up part of White Plains, centered on the Metro-North station, Mamaroneck Avenue, restaurants, shopping, and a growing collection of newer apartment buildings.\n\nCentral White Plains\n\nChurch Street\n\nChurch Street sits just off Downtown and shares much of its convenience, but at a slightly calmer scale.\n\nCentral White Plains\n\nGovernment Center\n\nGovernment Center is one of the most central parts of White Plains and gives the surrounding streets an established, civic feel.\n\nCentral White Plains\n\nHealth Center\n\nHealth Center is shaped by White Plains Hospital and the medical offices around it, which gives the area a familiar, everyday rhythm.\n\nCentral White Plains\n\nWinbrook\n\nWinbrook is close to the center of the city and has long been one of White Plains' better-known residential areas.\n\nCentral White Plains\n\nGateway\n\nGateway lives up to its name as the stretch between the city center and the residential neighborhoods around it.\n\nWest Side and Near-Downtown Neighborhoods\n\nBattle Hill"
