      "excerpt": "All viewpoints are welcome in this respectful, inclusive space designed to foster dialogue, reflection, and understanding.",
      "text": "All viewpoints are welcome in this respectful, inclusive space designed to foster dialogue, reflection, and understanding.\n\nLearning\n\nCommon Ground: Let's Discuss Local Housing Issues\n\nAll viewpoints are welcome in this respectful, inclusive space designed to foster dialogue, reflection, and understanding.\n\nAbout this event\n\nAll viewpoints are welcome in this respectful, inclusive space designed to foster dialogue, reflection, and understanding. Using the World Caf&eacute; model, participants will engage in small-group discussions guided by table captains, with opportunities to interact with a variety of voices throughout the evening. Check the library page for registration, tickets, and any schedule updates.\n\nAt a Glance\n\nStatus\n\nPast\n\nDate\n\nTuesday, April 14, 2026\n\nTime\n\n6:00 PM - 8:00 PM\n\nLocation\n\nWhite Plains Public Library, Auditorium\n\nAddress\n\n100 Martine Avenue, White Plains, NY 10601\n\nSource\n\nWhite Plains Public Library\n\nMore Events\n\nRelated events\n\nCreating a Compelling College Application this Summer\n\nApr 21, 2026\n\nProgram for High School Juniors: Creating a Compelling College Application this Summer We are offering this Zoom presentation to help high school juniors and…\n\nVirtual Poetry Open Mic\n\nApr 1, 2026\n\nJoin Zork and Tim for our monthly virtual Poetry Open Mic!\n\nArtificial Intelligence (A.I.) in the Igloo\n\nApr 9, 2026\n\nLearn about the current state of Artificial Intelligence (A.I.) and some of the exciting possibilities."
