      "text": "Across the U.S., librarians face the impact of uniting against library collection standards that include restrictions on race-related and LGBTQIA+ content.\n\nLearning\n\nFilm Screening: The Librarians\n\nAcross the U.S., librarians face the impact of uniting against library collection standards that include restrictions on race-related and LGBTQIA+ content.\n\nAbout this event\n\nAcross the U.S., librarians face the impact of uniting against library collection standards that include restrictions on race-related and LGBTQIA+ content. Join us for a screening of the award-winning documentary that will make you think deeply about the role of librarians, censorship, and our changing political landscape. The film screening will conclude with a community discussion of the important themes presented in The Librarians. This event is presented in partnership with the League of Women Voters and Indie Lens. Check the library page for registration, tickets, and any schedule updates.\n\nAt a Glance\n\nStatus\n\nPast\n\nDate\n\nSunday, April 19, 2026\n\nTime\n\n2:00 PM - 4:00 PM\n\nLocation\n\nWhite Plains Public Library, Auditorium\n\nAddress\n\n100 Martine Avenue, White Plains, NY 10601\n\nSource\n\nWhite Plains Public Library\n\nMore Events\n\nRelated events\n\nArtificial Intelligence (A.I.) in the Igloo\n\nApr 9, 2026\n\nLearn about the current state of Artificial Intelligence (A.I.) and some of the exciting possibilities.\n\nCommon Ground: Let's Discuss Local Housing Issues\n\nApr 14, 2026\n\nAll viewpoints are welcome in this respectful, inclusive space designed to foster dialogue, reflection, and understanding.\n\nCreating a Compelling College Application this Summer\n\nApr 21, 2026\n\nProgram for High School Juniors: Creating a Compelling College Application this Summer We are offering this Zoom presentation to help high school juniors and…"
