      "text": "The Friends presents The American Songbook featuring Gin Fizz: The &quot;Great American Songbook&quot; is the canon of the most important and influential…\n\nLearning\n\nFriends Spring Concert Presents: Gin Fizz\n\nThe Friends presents The American Songbook featuring Gin Fizz: The \"Great American Songbook\" is the canon of the most important and influential…\n\nAbout this event\n\nThe Friends presents The American Songbook featuring Gin Fizz: The \"Great American Songbook\" is the canon of the most important and influential American popular songs, jazz standards and theatre classics from the early 20th century. Gin Fizz plays these vintage gems with hip, youthful exuberance, while capturing the romance and sophistication of a bygone era. This band of virtuoso musicians is sure to delight music lovers both young and old with their warm and vibrant renditions of these captivating tunes. Check the library page for registration, tickets, and any schedule updates.\n\nAt a Glance\n\nStatus\n\nUpcoming\n\nDate\n\nSunday, May 3, 2026\n\nTime\n\n2:00 PM - 3:30 PM\n\nLocation\n\nWhite Plains Public Library, Auditorium\n\nAddress\n\n100 Martine Avenue, White Plains, NY 10601\n\nSource\n\nWhite Plains Public Library\n\nMore Events\n\nRelated events\n\nWhite Plains Sustainability Fair\n\nMay 16, 2026\n\nActivities: Make exploding wildflower seed balls Re-think eating and menus for healthier, sustainable food choices Watch composting demonstrations Learn about…\n\nRobert the Guitar Guy\n\nApr 29, 2026\n\nLocal favorite Robert the Guitar Guy comes to the Library!\n\nOver the Rainbow and Through the Woods\n\nMay 17, 2026\n\nPack your (imaginary) bags and join musical educator Rebecca Schoffer for a joyful, interactive sing-along celebrating Jewish American Heritage Month!"
