      "excerpt": "How to Protect Yourself against Housing Discrimination Learn how to recognize and protect yourself against housing discrimination.",
      "text": "How to Protect Yourself against Housing Discrimination Learn how to recognize and protect yourself against housing discrimination.\n\nLearning\n\nHow to Protect Yourself against Housing Discrimination\n\nHow to Protect Yourself against Housing Discrimination Learn how to recognize and protect yourself against housing discrimination.\n\nAbout this event\n\nHow to Protect Yourself against Housing Discrimination Learn how to recognize and protect yourself against housing discrimination. This program will provide an overview of your housing rights, common forms of discrimination, and practical steps you can take if you believe your rights have been violated. This program will also discuss timelines, mediation with landlords and local services available for those who are or may be facing eviction. Check the library page for registration, tickets, and any schedule updates.\n\nAt a Glance\n\nStatus\n\nUpcoming\n\nDate\n\nMonday, May 4, 2026\n\nTime\n\n6:00 PM - 7:00 PM\n\nLocation\n\nWhite Plains Public Library, Auditorium\n\nAddress\n\n100 Martine Avenue, White Plains, NY 10601\n\nSource\n\nWhite Plains Public Library\n\nMore Events\n\nRelated events\n\nWhite Plains in 1776 (History via Igloo)\n\nApr 22, 2026\n\nLearn about events in White Plains during the crucial year of 1776.\n\nLearn about 3D Printing (in the Igloo)\n\nApr 22, 2026\n\nLearn about 3D printing and how to use the Library's 3D printing services.\n\nThe Revolutionary: Samuel Adams by Stacy Schiff\n\nApr 25, 2026\n\nSpace is limited for this free event."
