      "text": "Were you a renter in 2021 and impacted by Hurricane Ida?\n\nLearning\n\nRenter Safe Housing Incentive Program\n\nWere you a renter in 2021 and impacted by Hurricane Ida?\n\nAbout this event\n\nWere you a renter in 2021 and impacted by Hurricane Ida? The Rental Safe Housing Incentive Program can help you move to a safer home. Up to $50,000 in financial assistance is available for those who qualify. Join us and let our team guide you through the application process-getting started is easier than you think! Questions? Email: Intake@communityhousing.org or (845) 330-3948 Ext. 3004. Check the library page for registration, tickets, and any schedule updates.\n\nAt a Glance\n\nStatus\n\nUpcoming\n\nDate\n\nTuesday, April 28, 2026\n\nTime\n\n5:00 PM - 7:00 PM\n\nLocation\n\nWhite Plains Public Library, Community Room\n\nAddress\n\n100 Martine Avenue, White Plains, NY 10601\n\nSource\n\nWhite Plains Public Library\n\nMore Events\n\nRelated events\n\nWhite Plains Sustainability Fair\n\nMay 16, 2026\n\nActivities: Make exploding wildflower seed balls Re-think eating and menus for healthier, sustainable food choices Watch composting demonstrations Learn about…\n\nWhite Plains in 1776 (History via Igloo)\n\nApr 22, 2026\n\nLearn about events in White Plains during the crucial year of 1776.\n\nLifting Up Westchester\n\nApr 22, 2026\n\nVictor Ortiz of Lifting Up Westchester will be available to provide information about essential social services available to patrons in the White Plains area."
