      "text": "Space is limited for this free event.\n\nLearning\n\nThe Revolutionary: Samuel Adams by Stacy Schiff\n\nSpace is limited for this free event.\n\nAbout this event\n\nSpace is limited for this free event. Register Here to attend. Note: Seats are not assigned but first come, first served. You can hold a ticket for up to one other guest. Please be prepared to sign in to Eventbrite to reserve your seat. This event is presented by public libraries throughout Westchester County in coordination with the Revolutionary Westchester 250 initiative. Reserve a copy of The Revolutionary: Samuel Adams from any Westchester library. A selection of books written by both authors can be purchased and signed at the event, or you can bring your own copy. Check the library page for registration, tickets, and any schedule updates.\n\nAt a Glance\n\nStatus\n\nUpcoming\n\nDate\n\nSaturday, April 25, 2026\n\nTime\n\n3:00 PM - 4:30 PM\n\nLocation\n\nWhite Plains Public Library, Ask Staff For More Information\n\nAddress\n\n100 Martine Avenue, White Plains, NY 10601\n\nSource\n\nWhite Plains Public Library\n\nMore Events\n\nRelated events\n\nWhite Plains in 1776 (History via Igloo)\n\nApr 22, 2026\n\nLearn about events in White Plains during the crucial year of 1776.\n\nLearn about 3D Printing (in the Igloo)\n\nApr 22, 2026\n\nLearn about 3D printing and how to use the Library's 3D printing services.\n\nWuthering Heights Tea Party & Discussion\n\nApr 28, 2026\n\nThe recent movie adaptation of Emily Bront&euml;'s novel Wuthering Heights has brought renewed interest to the enduring classic."
